<HL>
   Zapata Corp. to Redeem Bonds
</HL>
<DATE>
09/27/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE C19
</SO>
<CO>
   ZOS
</CO>
<IN>
OIL EQUIPMENT AND SERVICES (OIE)
PETROLEUM (PET)
BUYBACKS, REDEMPTIONS, SWAP OFFERS (BBK)
</IN>
<LP>
   HOUSTON -- Zapata Corp. said it would redeem on Nov. 1
about $27.6 million face amount of its 8 5/8% U.S. government
guaranteed ship financing bonds, due June 15, 1996.
   The energy company said it will pay 101.815% of the
principal, plus interest accrued from June 15, or about
$1,050.73 for each of the $1,000 bonds.
</LP>
