   The key U.S. and foreign annual interest rates below are a
guide to general levels but don't always represent actual
transactions.
                                                                                                       

   PRIME RATE: 10%. The base rate on corporate loans at large
U.S. money center commercial banks.
                                                                                                       

   FFEDERAL FUNDS: 8 1/4% high, 8 1/8% low, 8 1/8% near
closing bid, 8 3/16% offered. Reserves traded among
commercial banks for overnight use in amounts of $1 million
or more. Source: Babcock Fulton Prebon (U.S.A.) Inc.
                                                                                                       

   DISCOUNT RATE: 7%. The charge on loans to depository
institutions by the New York Federal Reserve Bank.
                                                                                                       

   CALL MONEY: 9 1/4% to 9 1/2%. The charge on loans to
brokers on stock exchange collateral.
                                                                                                       

   COMMERCIAL PAPER placed directly by General Motors
Acceptance Corp.: 8.125% 30 to 44 days; 8% 45 to 59 days;
7.90% 60 to 89 days; 7.85% 90 to 119 days; 7.80% 120 to 149
days; 7.75% 150 to 179 days; 7.65% 180 to 270 days.
                                                                                                       

   COMMERCIAL PAPER: High-grade unsecured notes sold through
dealers by major corporations in multiples of $1,000: 8.31%
30 days; 8.24% 60 days; 8.18% 90 days.
                                                                                                       

   CERTIFICATES OF DEPOSIT: 7.72% one month; 7.72% two
months; 7.72% three months; 7.78% six months; 7.94% one year.
Average of top rates paid by major New York banks on primary
new issues of negotiable C.D.s, usually on amounts of $1
million and more. The minimum unit is $100,000. Typical rates
in the secondary market: 8.30% one month; 8.30% three months;
8.30% six months.
                                                                                                       

   BANKERS ACCEPTANCES: 8.28% 30 days; 8.16% 60 days; 8.07%
90 days; 8.06% 120 days; 7.98% 150 days; 7.92% 180 days.
Negotiable, bank-backed business credit instruments typically
financing an import order.
                                                                                                       

   LONDON LATE EURODOLLARS: 8 1/2% - 8 3/8% one month; 8 1/2%
- 8 3/8% two months; 8 1/2% - 8 3/8% three months; 8 1/2% - 8
3/8% four months; 8 1/2% - 8 3/8% five months; 8 1/2% - 8
3/8% six months.
                                                                                                       

   LONDON INTERBANK OFFERED RATES (LIBOR): 8 1/2% one month;
8 1/2% three months; 8 1/2% six months; 8 9/16% one year. The
average of interbank offered rates for dollar deposits in the
London market based on quotations at five major banks.
                                                                                                       

   FOREIGN PRIME RATES: Canada 13.75%; Germany 10.50%; Japan
7.38%; Switzerland 8.75%; Britain 15%. These rate indications
aren't directly comparable; lending practices vary widely by
location.
                                                                                                       

   TREASURY BILLS: Results of the Monday, September 24, 1990,
auction of short-term U.S. government bills, sold at a
discount from face value in units of $10,000 to $1 million:
7.32% 13 weeks; 7.33% 26 weeks.
                                                                                                       

   FEDERAL HOME LOAN MORTGAGE CORP. (Freddie Mac): Posted
yields on 30-year mortgage commitments for delivery within 30
days. 10.26%, standard conventional fixed-rate mortgages;
8.25%, 2% rate capped one-year adjustable rate mortgages.
Source: Telerate Systems Inc.
                                                                                                       

