   NEW HAVEN, Conn. -- United Illuminating Co., a utility,
said it purchased $97.9 million of its 12% debentures, due
2017, as part of a program to reduce debt.
   The company also purchased $80.4 million principal amount
of its 10.5% debentures, due 1995, and $11.8 million
principal amount of its 10.25% debentures, due 2000, in
open-market transactions. It estimated that these
transactions will produce pretax savings of nearly $6
million.
