   Business Brief -- Tecumseh Products Co.:
   Third-Period Loss Expected
   Of as Much as $16 Million
</HL>
<DATE>
09/27/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   TECU
</CO>
<IN>
ELECTRICAL COMPONENTS AND EQUIPMENT (ELQ)
</IN>
<LP>
   Tecumseh Products Co. said it will have a third-quarter
loss of about $14 million to $16 million, after taking a
$19.2 million charge for an environmental cleanup near a
plant.
   The Tecumseh, Mich., maker of compressors, engines and
pumps said the per-share loss will be about $2.50 to $3.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   The charge, which comes to $3.51 a share, goes to clean up
PCB contamination in the Sheboygan River near a Tecumseh
die-casting plant. The plant used PCB, a suspected
carcinogen, as a fire retardant in the 1950s and 1960s.
   Tecumseh had net income of $27 million, or $4.94 a share,
in the first half of 1990.
