<HL>
   Witco Puts Richardson on Block
</HL>
<DATE>
09/27/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   WIT
</CO>
<IN>
TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)
CHEMICALS, PLASTICS (CHM)
</IN>
<LP>
   NEW YORK -- Witco Corp., a specialty chemicals and
petroleum company, said that it plans to sell its Richardson
Co. subsidiary, a maker of injection molded plastic and
rubber battery containers and accessories, and that it
engaged Smith Barney, Harris Upham &amp; Co. to assist in the
sale.
   In 1989, Richardson had sales of $66.3 million. Witco had
sales of $798 million for the six months ended June 30. A
Witco spokesman said the Richardson business, part of an
acquisition made in the early 1980s, "doesn't fit our
strategic core businesses" and might be more appropriate for
a battery maker or injection molding company.
</LP>
