assumed by the taxpayers, a Treasury official said in
outlining proposed changes to the federal deposit insurance
system.
   ---
   The SEC wants to force companies to account for assets
using more current rather than historical values. The banking
industry, the agency's first target, is fighting the change.
   ---
   General Electric hid serious doubts about its design of a
nuclear containment vessel, a judge ruled, calling GE's
conduct "unconscionable." The decision raises the firm's
exposure to potential damages.
   ---
   Orders for durable goods fell 0.8% in August despite a big
jump in orders for defense equipment. Personal income and
spending, meanwhile, failed to keep pace with inflation.
   ---
   Milken should receive a prison term longer than Boesky's
three-year sentence, prosecutors urged.
   ---
