   U.S. stock prices tumbled as oil markets rallied on rising
expectations of supply disruptions. The Dow Jones industrials
fell 25.99 points.
   ---
   Conflict-of-interest rules allegedly violated by Neil Bush
as an S&amp;L official don't explicitly bar the ties he had with
borrowers, regulators said.
   ---
   Stock offerings plunged in the third quarter to $3.2
billion thus far in the period, 48% less than a year ago.
