   Fidelity Investments is seeking to change the objective of
its junk-bond fund to focus on appreciation, not just high
yields. Other mutual fund groups are likely to copy the move.
   ---
   BankAmerica apparently won the government's auction of
MeraBank, once Arizona's biggest S&amp;L, with a bid thought to
exceed $81 million.
   ---
   Arbitragers holding Corroon stock are using an obscure
Delaware law to try to derail the company's stock-swap merger
with Willis Faber.
   ---
   USAir suspended its dividend and deferred for several
years the delivery of 16 new Boeing aircraft.
   ---
   Alan Bond resigned as chairman of Bond Corp. Holdings,
apparently to pave the way for a restructuring of the
foundering Australian company.
   ---
   Bush moved to begin negotiating a free-trade agreement
with Mexico under "fast-track" procedures.
