<HL>
   Business Brief -- Pier 1 Imports Inc.:
   Stake in Sunbelt Nursery
   Bought for $22.7 Million
</HL>
<DATE>
09/27/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   PIR SBN IMI
</CO>
<IN>
TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)
SPECIALTY RETAILERS (OTS)
DIVIDENDS (DIV)
</IN>
<LP>
   After buying the Sunbelt Nursery Group Inc. from Tandy
Corp. in 1975 and spinning it off 10 years later, Pier 1
Imports Inc. bought back a controlling stake for $22.7
million.
   Pier 1 purchased 1,891,896 shares, or 50.4%, of Sunbelt
common stock outstanding at $12 a share from Intermark Inc.
of La Jolla, Calif., which is also Pier 1's largest
shareholder. Pier 1 will begin a tender offer no later than
Oct. 2 for the approximately 1,860,000 remaining shares of
Sunbelt at $12 a share.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Pier 1, a home-furnishing retailer and importer, will
operate Sunbelt as a subsidiary and combine certain aspects
of both businesses, said Pier 1 Chairman and Chief Executive
Officer Clark A. Johnson. Both companies are based in Fort
Worth.
   Separately, Intermark said it will not pay a quarterly
cash dividend for October on its common or participating
preferred stock. Intermark paid a three-cent dividend last
quarter.
