   International Brief -- Cie. Generale d'Electricite:
   French Concern Says Profit
   For Six Months Fell 24%
</HL>
<DATE>
09/27/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   F.CGE
</CO>
<IN>
ELECTRIC UTILITIES (ELC)
EARNINGS (ERN)
</IN>
<LP>
   Generale d'Electricite said profit after payments to
minority interests was 1.98 billion French francs ($376.3
million) for the first half of the year, down 24% from 2.59
billion francs in the year-earlier period.
   The French electricity and telecommunications group noted
that profit in the year-ago period reflected heavy
exceptional gains related to the creation of GECAlsthom S.A.,
a joint venture with General Electric PLC. General Electric
PLC is not related to General Electric Co. of the U.S.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Revenue rose 2% to 68.55 billion francs from 67.17 billion
francs.
   The company said it expects full-year net profit on a
comparable basis to continue to grow at the same pace as in
1989, despite economic uncertainties linked to higher oil
prices.
