   Business Brief -- J2 Communications:
   Entertainment Firm Revises
   Offer for National Lampoon
</HL>
<DATE>
09/27/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   NLPI JTWO
</CO>
<IN>
RECREATION, ENTERTAINMENT, TOYS, MOVIES, PHOTOGRAPHY, SPORTS (REC)
TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)
</IN>
<LP>
   J2 Communications, an entertainment concern, said it
modified slightly its $4.7 million offer to acquire National
Lampoon Inc.
   Under terms of the original and the revised offers,
shareholders of the New York-based humor magazine would
receive two-thirds of a share of J2 common stock plus a
warrant for each share of Lampoon currently held. The revised
offer lowered the exercise price of the warrant to $3.25 a
share from $3.75 a share.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   The modification reflects a minor change in the relative
value of the two companies' stocks since the agreement was
reached in March, J2 said. National Lampoon's shares have
fallen to $1.75 bid from $3.125 bid in over-the-counter
trading. J2's shares have dropped to $1.875 bid from $3 bid.
   Shareholders of both companies will vote on the
transaction at meetings set for Oct. 24 in Los Angeles.
